			<dc:subject>Apps</dc:subject>
			<description>I've recently been spending a &lt;em&gt;lot&lt;/em&gt; of time in the various virtualization apps -- &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.vmware.com/mac&quot;&gt;VMware Fusion&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.parallels.com/products/desktop/&quot;&gt;Parallels Desktop&lt;/a&gt;, and Sun &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.virtualbox.org&quot;&gt;VirtualBox&lt;/a&gt;. VirtualBox was recently upgraded to version 2.0.6, and after upgrading, I had issues with my Vista guest OS on my Mac Pro, which was previously working fine.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Whenever I chose to sleep or shut down Vista, the progress bar would move a bit at first, then jump back to the main VirtualBox window, where the Vista VM's status would read &quot;Aborted.&quot; (Somewhat interestingly, the exact same installation of Vista on my MacBook Pro doesn't exhibit this issue under 2.0.6.)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;After some searching, I found &lt;a href=&quot;http://forums.virtualbox.org/viewtopic.php?p=48153&amp;amp;sid=47b2bda5d305660c7bc0bbc5477595e3&quot;&gt;this thread&lt;/a&gt; on the VirtualBox forums that described the exact same problem. User withfries2, who poste...&lt;br clear=&quot;both&quot; style=&quot;clear: both;&quot;/&gt;
