		<item>
			<title>Toggle 'Show Cover Page During 2-up' in Acrobat</title>
			<link>http://feeds.macosxhints.com/click.phdo?i=5323b15c5ee5caab4501d7e495a0d542</link>
			<pheedo:origLink>http://www.macosxhints.com/article.php?story=20081205121929624</pheedo:origLink>
			<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.macosxhints.com/article.php?story=20081205121929624</guid>
			<pubDate>Tue, 09 Dec 2008 07:30:00 -0800</pubDate>
			<comments>http://www.macosxhints.com/article.php?story=20081205121929624#comments</comments>
			<dc:subject>Apps</dc:subject>
			<description>When viewing book PDFs with the facing-pages (two-up) view option, one usually wants left-facing pages to be on the left so that spreads are viewed as they would be in a printed copy. Unfortunately, Acrobat 8 often defaults to the opposite. This simple AppleScript toggles the View menu option &lt;em&gt;Show Cover Page During 2-up&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;div style=&quot;margin-left: 20px; margin-top:10px; margin-bottom:10px; padding: 5px; border:1px solid; width:520px; height:120px; overflow:scroll;white-space:nowrap&quot;&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Drag-select from top-to-bottom, then copy, and paste into Script Editor&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;--Toggle 'Show Cover Page During 2-up' optiontell application &quot;Adobe Acrobat Professional&quot;  activate  tell front document    tell application &quot;System Events&quot;      tell process &quot;Adobe Acrobat Professional&quot;                tell menu bar 1          tell menu bar item &quot;View&quot;            tell menu 1              tell menu item &quot;Page Display&quot;                tell menu 1                  click menu item &quot;Show Cover ...&lt;br style=&quot;clear: both;&quot;/&gt;
  &lt;a style='font-size: 10px; color: maroon;' href='http://www.pheedo.com/hostedMorselClick.php?hfmm=v3:efd357dd7c9c0eb50f6061e8d0bf3ed1:7XN87vikTsMCGvGvfO3eNR6OBi2xa5W9PamnR7a1NKXX9m%2FMyvs8naAFbHdHMhB9wVBcSKIpcHoz'&gt;&lt;img border='0' title='Add to digg' alt='Add to digg' src='http://www.pheedo.com/images/mm/digg.gif'/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
